<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">This was originally a response to the Bard thread in the General/OT forum, but eh, it's more of a rant.
<br />

<br />
Bards can do almost everything far better than we can. Their haste spell in a single group scenario is simply better (since it increases nuke damage as well as taking you past the haste cap), their mana regen is at least comparable, and they've got equal mezzing abilities unless you're pulling 3 or more mobs. On top of that, if the shit hits the fan, they've got plate armor (okay, we've got Arcane/Eldritch to mitigate this difference somewhat), a deftdance discipline (er....guess we don't get the equivalent of that...maybe Doppelganger?), Fading Memories (um...mem blurs are sort of like a shitty version of this...), and Divine Aura (I ran dry on enchanter defensive abilities).
<br />

<br />
The "but they can only sing four songs at once" is not really a disadvantage in the single group situation, since you usually have one or two other support classes capable of picking up the bard's slack. If you have a shaman, the bard doesn't have to slow, and he can rotate out the haste song without losing too much when he needs to mez; if you've got a ranger, he doesn't have to snare; add a monk and he doesn't have to pull; toss in an enchanter and he won't ever have to mez and his mana song won't be missed as much, etc. Notice that none of the classes you added to the group actually REPLACED the bard, or DUPLICATED his abilities in any way, but simply made him switch to doing something else (something else that's equally good).
<br />

<br />
In fact, when you think about the sheer volume of a bard's ability, it's sort of sick:
<br />

<br />
Need a snarer? get a bard.
<br />
Need more DPS? get a bard.
<br />
Need a puller? get a bard.
<br />
Need some crowd control? get a bard.
<br />
Need less downtime? get a bard.
<br />
Need a slower? get a bard.
<br />
Need help travelling? get a bard.
<br />
Need some resist buffs? get a bard.
<br />
Need resist debuffs? get a bard.
<br />

<br />
The only thing they can't do atm is tank, heal, and charm. And, hey, I can't tank and heal either. Or snare. Or pull (as well as they can). Or travel (as well as they can). And so on...Seems like an awful lot to trade for charm spells I can't even use in most of the new expansion.
<br />

<br />
I love my enchanter a lot. But the number of group roles bards can fill and their raid stackability is, frankly, FAR more than any other class in the game. It'd be fine if they were a lot worse than me at crowd control, but they're not. The fact of the matter is, on that 4 pull you use AE bliss to lock down, a bard could have pulled 3, or 2, or 1, using lull, fading, highsun, snare, or any of their host of pulling tools. Or he could have pulled 4, gotten enough agro to kite 3 using one of their nice AE songs with high agro, let the puller tank one, and supplied the group with better haste than you add, nuke damage, and mana regen while he kited.
<br />

<br />
I don't hate bards. Spare me the "well if their so gud u play 1 than". I'm not a power hungry tool looking for the 'm0st ub4r' class - I enjoy my enchanter and the challenge he presents. I just think the bard class is a mockery of balance. Charmed uber-pookas are NOTHING compared to the single pulls I have seen my bard friends make in KT (which zone did you want this mob at?), or the fact that they're the best pullers for our raids as well, and even if their ability to pull were in some way nerfed, they'd still have no shortage of things to do.
<br />

<br />
I think the only reason they've gotten away with it so far is there are so few of them that they are generally shunted around rather then directly replacing anyone. Got a monk who can pull decently? Great! The bard could do it better, but, eh, our dps is kind of lacking today and it'd be awesome to have him in our rogue group. What's that? Plenty of Enchanters to mez? Awesome, we'll put the bards on resist songs then, a bunch of our new members are undergeared. We don't need that bard increasing our nuking DPS in the wizard group? Sweet, shift him over to the cleric group where he can make their mana regen better, we're short on healing tonight.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
<br />
