<span class="postbody">You can use your same argument for Druids over chanters. Only advantage the cleric has is rez. Druids can buff, they can heal, they can DS, they can increase run seppd, and they can TP people. Why for god's sake would anyone want a Cleric in their group?
<br />

<br />
I can buff my group with haste, MR, charisma, and mana regen plus one very nice combat buff with NDT. THen I can go off and do ANYTHING the group requires. If there is a shaman or beastlord, i can let them slow and go get a HIGH DPS pet. If not, I can STILL get  a high DPS pet and slow as well. I can provide Crowd Control AND I can be puller. And I can do it ALL without spamming the group with song spam.
<br />

<br />
But the greatest advantage of all that I have over a bard. I can atually talk to people while I play the game.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
