<br />
Slow mob
<br />
Nuke mob.
<br />

<br />
Add one -
<br />

<br />
Mez, tash mob, slow mob.
<br />

<br />
Add two - mez, tash mob, slow mob.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
For a 3 song bard -- 
<br />

<br />
Warsong of Zek (think vallons with a DS) - haste
<br />
Wind of Marr (c5 but a little better) - mind candy
<br />
Call of the muse (DD/DoT booster / overhaste)
<br />

<br />
Drop one and add slow.
<br />
Drop another if the mob resists
<br />
Drop another if the bard needs to debuff the mobs MR slightly to slow.
<br />

<br />
Add one - bard has to drop a song to keep the target mezzed.
<br />

<br />
Add two - bard has to drop 2 songs.
<br />

<br />
Oh wait, now the group isnt hasted or DD boosted / overhaste.
<br />

<br />

<br />
An ench can do that.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
Besides, have you ever played a bard past 40??   4 song twists is hellish to keep up for more than an hour or two.
<br />
3 song twists is alright, but still it wears on you after a while, if you get sleepy you miss twists, dropping your overall efficiency.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Its like comparing apples and oranges really.  Bards may be the closest class to us but they arent anything like us.  They pay a huge price for what they do, just like we pay a huge price to do what we do.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
